entry.title: [omnibox] Moves header toggle state pref observation to OmniboxEditModel
entry.content:
Follow up to crrev.com/c/4632098



Ideally, the view should not be observing the pref directly. This CL

makes OmniboxEditModel observe that pref and notify OmniboxPopupView

to update itself. OmniboxPopupView in turn updates OmniboxResultView

and OmniboxHeaderView and its own layout. For that to happen, this CL

refactors OmniboxHeaderView which is internal to OmniboxRowView into

its own file and provides an accessor to it like for OmniboxResultView.



Also moves setting and reading the header toggle state to the

OmniboxController.

entry.title: webauthn: don't prelink in work profiles.
entry.content:
When Chrome is running in an Android work profile, it would still

publish prelinking information. This can cause Chrome on the desktop to

select that instance of Chrome to connect to for hybrid transactions,

but from inside of a work profile, only work profile passkeys can be

used. Thus this change suppresses publishing any pre-linking information

from inside a work profile.

entry.title: [ SavedTabGroups ] Fix bug for synced devices displaying wrong tab order
entry.content:
When a SavedTab is reordered in the Tabstrip we would only notify sync of the tab that was moved. This lead to inconsistency across devices as they would move the tab to the correct position but fail to update the positions of the other tabs that were not moved. This happens when a user moves multiple tabs in quick succession (Think of the ball and cups magic trick).



Additionally, every time we reorder a group in the bookmarks bar, all data about the groups including the tabs were synced. While this method will ensure ordering it is also highly expensive as we only need to keep track of the group reorders and not the tabs in this case.



Fix:

- Add a new observer function SavedTabGroupTabsReorderedLocally

- Remove tab notifications when a SavedTabGroup is reordered

- Notify sync of all the tab positions when a SavedTab is reordered in the Tabstrip

Users can snap browser windows to the desktop and the user can

manage app's position/size via resize grip. The position/size

If the position or size is changed, the window pops out and resize

grip can't be used anymore.

entry.content:
When loading unpacked extensions, we don't validate all locales.

default locale, the developer won't be notified. In order to ensure

they are working, developers need to manually change Chrome's

locale for every single supported one.

validate them at once.

entry.title: webauthn: don't assume that requests have an AndroidWindow.
entry.content:
In 0e4ad7ebea, the `getContext` function[1] was lifted up to

`AuthenticatorFactory`. That function had assumed that the window of a

`WebContents` that made a FIDO request was non-null, but it was only

called in CredMan paths. After 0e4ad7ebea, that assumption was used for

all requests. Based on crbug.com/1459476, the assumption was invalid and

the AndroidWindow can be null for unclear reasons. (Perhaps navigation

during a request?)



Either way, we mirror the behaviour prior to 0e4ad7ebea and use the

application context when the window is unavailable.



[1] https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4638672/12/components/webauthn/android/java/src/org/chromium/components/webauthn/Fido2CredentialRequest.java#b1380

entry.title: [a11y] Serialize text deletion/insertion offsets for accessibility
entry.content:
This CL adds logic to notify accessibility of changes in text range's

offset with respect to their anchor nodes.



This is to fix a UIA bug where the text offset in

the `TextRangeProvider` is out of sync when a deletion is made, which

then leads to some ATs that expect the text range to be synched with

the renderer to have wrong behavior.



The way this is done in this CL is:

1) When a deletion is made through a backspace command, we notify the

`AXObjectCache` of the deletion, if the cache already exists.

This is also done if an insertion happens.

2) The `AXObjectCache` then sends a tree update with information

on where the deletion/insertion has happened. This information

is sent through new IntList attributes that were added in this CL.

3) On the browser side, we notify observers when this is

received, and these update the offset accordingly when necessary.

entry.title: ash: Fix a leak in DesksTest.DragMiniViewWhileRemoving
entry.content:
This test removes a desk while in overview mode and then attempts to

drag it. In order to make the drag part meaningful in the test, it

overrides the animation duration to be `NORMAL_DURATION`.



When a desk is removed, a self deleting `RemovedMiniViewAnimation`

object is created. It is implicitly owned by the animation and deletes

itself when the animation completes. When Jelly is enabled, the test

ends before the animation has completed and the animation object leaks.



The test was fixed by adding an observer that waits until all animations

in the `DeskMiniView` has completed.

entry.title: DeskButton: Ensure proper formatting on button
entry.content:
This CL ensures that the desk button has the correct formatting.

Previously, we used FlexLayout and did not show a DeskSwitchButton if we

were on the far left or far right desks. This caused for the FlexLayout

to not account for the invisible button, so it would give more space to

the desk name label. This CL fixes this by changing the visibility state

logic to opacity state and enabled state logic so that the FlexLayout

accounts for invisible buttons. This CL also ensures that the

HotseatWidget is reserving the correct amount of space in the vertical

shelf by having the DeskButtonWidget::GetPreferredLength function

account for whether the shelf is horizontal. Finally, this CL adds a

unit test in desks_unittests.cc to verify that everything is positioned

correctly.

entry.title: Use a fixed flat set to store stopwords.
entry.content:
This is more memory efficient than std::unordered_set and requires no

heap allocations. However, since the list of stop words is quite long,

sorting it dynamically at compile time exceeds the maximum number of

steps allowed in constexpr evaluation. To work around this, add

MakeFixedFlatSetSorted() which requires already sorted input as an

analogue to the already-existing MakeFixedFlatMapSorted().
